"    [theme=dark] .colab-df-convert:hover {\n","      background-color: #434B5C;\n","      box-shadow: 0px 1px 3px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);\n","      filter: drop-shadow(0px 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3));\n","      fill: #FFFFFF;\n","    }\n","  </style>\n","\n","      <script>\n","        const buttonEl =\n","          document.querySelector('#df-afe6d68f-4a19-4a41-9f6e-d98f0d2398f1 button.colab-df-convert');\n","        buttonEl.style.display =\n","          google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n","\n","        async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n","          const element = document.querySelector('#df-afe6d68f-4a19-4a41-9f6e-d98f0d2398f1');\n","          const dataTable =\n","            await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n","                                                     [key], {});\n","          if (!dataTable) return;\n","\n","          const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n","            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n","            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n","          element.innerHTML = '';\n","          dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n","          await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n","          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n","          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n","          element.appendChild(docLink);\n","        }\n","      </script>\n","    </div>\n","  </div>\n","  "],"text/plain":["                open  ...  seasonal Difference for close\n","date                  ...                               \n","2013-02-08  390.4551  ...                            NaN\n","2013-02-11  389.5892  ...                            NaN\n","2013-02-12  391.2659  ...                            NaN\n","2013-02-13  390.4551  ...                            NaN\n","2013-02-14  390.2549  ...                            NaN\n","\n","[5 rows x 12 columns]"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":46}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["the data in not seasonal the"],"metadata":{"id":"K_wIXRTWSu10"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# 12 Parameter Selection in time series"],"metadata":{"id":"yHfDIkk8Oq0Z"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["The optimal lag to use to make a relatively stationary version of our original time series"],"metadata":{"id":"rTljTBqyr8XE"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"ZWtHeXw0r00Q"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Parameter Selection for the ARIMA Time Series Model which are (p, d, q). These three parameters account for seasonality, trend, and noise in data:Making autocorrelation and partial autocorrelation charts help us choose hyperparameters for the ARIMA model.\n","\n","The ACF gives us a measure of how much each \"y\" value is correlated to the previous n \"y\" values prior.\n","\n","The PACF is the partial correlation function gives us (a sample of) the amount of correlation between two \"y\" values separated by n lags excluding the impact of all the \"y\" values in between them."],"metadata":{"id":"xW-wiCbJPBFD"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["To determine p, q, d:\n","\n","- AR model might be investigated first with lag length selected from the PACF or  via empirical investigation. In our case, it's clearly that within 0 lags the AR is significant. Which means, we can use AR = 0\n","- MA order (in the case where the MA is first tried then the MA order is being set to 1\n"],"metadata":{"id":"rnSJLQdUaUBm"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["so the ACF and PACF gives us p as 1 and q as 1 so we will build ARIMa model on the basis of this"],"metadata":{"id":"SMLk2GOtSYBu"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import itertools\n","# Define the d and q parameters to take any value between 0 and 1\n","q = d = range(0, 2)\n","# Define the p parameters to take any value between 0 and 3\n","p = range(0, 4)\n","\n","# Generate all different combinations of p, q and q triplets\n","pdq = list(itertools.product(p, d, q))\n","\n","# Generate all different combinations of seasonal p, q and q triplets\n","seasonal_pdq = [(x[0], x[1], x[2], 12) for x in list(itertools.product(p, d, q))]\n","\n","print('parameter combinations for Seasonal ARIMA...')\n","print('SARIMAX: {} x {}'.format(pdq[1], seasonal_pdq[1]))\n","print('SARIMAX: {} x {}'.format(pdq[1], seasonal_pdq[2]))\n","print('SARIMAX: {} x {}'.format(pdq[2], seasonal_pdq[3]))\n","print('SARIMAX: {} x {}'.format(pdq[2], seasonal_pdq[4]))"],"metadata":{"id":"4NaY9TENglkU","outputId":"8fbe87d3-16e0-40d3-b024-365993885349","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["parameter combinations for Seasonal ARIMA...\n","SARIMAX: (0, 0, 1) x (0, 0, 1, 12)\n","SARIMAX: (0, 0, 1) x (0, 1, 0, 12)\n","SARIMAX: (0, 1, 0) x (0, 1, 1, 12)\n","SARIMAX: (0, 1, 0) x (1, 0, 0, 12)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#l_param = []\n","#l_param_seasonal=[]\n","#l_results_aic=[]\n","#for param in pdq:\n","   # for param_seasonal in seasonal_pdq:\n","       # try:\n","           # mod = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(train_data,\n","                                            #order=param,\n","                                           # seasonal_order=param_seasonal,\n","                                            #enforce_stationarity=False,\n","                                            #enforce_invertibility=False)\n","\n","            #results = mod.fit()\n","\n","            #print('ARIMA{}x{}12 - AIC:{}'.format(param, param_seasonal, results.aic))\n","\n","           # l_param.append(param)\n","            #l_param_seasonal.append(param_seasonal)\n","           # l_results_aic.append(results.aic)\n","       # except:\n","          #  continue"],"metadata":{"id":"ijiUBmR99Ilo"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Plug the optimal parameter values into a new SARIMAX model\n","#ARIMA_MODEL = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(train_data,\n","#                                        order=(3, 1, 1),\n","                                        #seasonal_order=(3, 1, 1, 12),\n","                                        #enforce_stationarity=False,\n","                                        #enforce_invertibility=False)\n","\n","# Fit the model and print results\n","#output = ARIMA_MODEL.fit()\n","\n","#print(output.summary().tables[1])"],"metadata":{"id":"i1HyO1XEgh1c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Call plot_diagnostics() on the results calculated above\n","#output.plot_diagnostics(figsize=(15, 18))\n","#plt.show()"],"metadata":{"id":"EuaNCpCggiAB"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","Let's check for these assumptions from diagnostics plots.\n","\n","In the top right plot, we see that the red KDE line follows closely with the N(0,1) line (where N(0,1)) is the standard notation for a normal distribution with mean 0 and standard deviation of 1). This is a good indication that the residuals are normally distributed.\n","\n","The normal qq-plot on the bottom left shows that the ordered distribution of residuals (blue dots) follows the linear trend of the samples taken from a standard normal distribution with N(0, 1). Again, this is a strong indication that the residuals are normally distributed.\n","\n","The residuals over time (top left plot) don't display any obvious seasonality and appear to be white noise.  The time series residuals have low correlation with lagged versions of itself.\n","\n","To conclude that  model has no correlations and provides a satisfactory fit to help forecast future values."],"metadata":{"id":"VNxm9XPam1Vi"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#preds = output.fittedvalues"],"metadata":{"id":"D4PlzNMSEQKx"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#GOOGL_Sea['predictions'] = GOOGL[GOOGL.columns[1]] * (1 + preds)\n","#GOOGL_Sea['predictions'].head()\n"],"metadata":{"id":"BsLTG8HJGYum"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["##import plotly.graph_objects as go\n","#WINDOW_LENGTH = 100\n","\n","#fig = go.Figure()\n","#fig.add_trace(go.Line(x=GOOGL_Sea.index[-WINDOW_LENGTH:], y=GOOGL_Sea[-WINDOW_LENGTH:], name='Actual',\n","                         #line=dict(color='blue', width=1)))\n","#fig.add_trace(go.Line(x=GOOGL_Sea.index[-WINDOW_LENGTH:], y=preds[-WINDOW_LENGTH:], name = 'Predictions',\n","                         #line=dict(color='red', width=1)\n","#))\n","\n","#fig.update_layout(title='Predictions vs Actual Returns',\n","                  # xaxis_title='Year')\n","#fig.show()"],"metadata":{"id":"vJaZz5N_E4fo"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#13 Test for Reseduial"],"metadata":{"id":"zNLgIA0e2Pza"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#residuals = abs(GOOGL_Sea['predictions']- GOOGL['close'])"],"metadata":{"id":"DfY-bZf32Vbr"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#plt.hist(residuals.values, bins=100)\n","#plt.show();"],"metadata":{"id":"ZVwguSRH2cgC"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#residuals.plot(kind='kde')"],"metadata":{"id":"0HWgUaAJodA9"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#residuals.describe()"],"metadata":{"id":"yYbZZXIcosk8"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#plot_pacf(residuals)"],"metadata":{"id":"wqQBBmMtoyWV"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["The mean of the residual is close to Zero and there is no significant correlation also that we can see in the pacf plot for residuals"],"metadata":{"id":"GLcSE4gcolw9"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#14 Evaluation"],"metadata":{"id":"_ExijDcHisJg"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#y_test=test_data\n","#y_pred = GOOGL_Sea['predictions']\n","#print(y_test.shape, y_pred.shape)\n"